<item>
            <title>[LU-15280] &quot;lfs changelog --follow&quot; does not support wrapped llog catalog</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15280</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a changelog_catalog become wrapped, &quot;lfs changelog --follow&quot; / &quot;llapi_changelog_recv with CHANGELOG_FLAG_FOLLOW&quot; stop at the last changelog record before the wrapping.&lt;br/&gt;
It does not dequeue records at the beginning of changelogs catalogs (in the plain llogs).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue has been seen in production with Lustre 2.12.6 and Robinhood.&lt;br/&gt;
I have reproduced this issue on Lustre master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this issue could affect some other functionalities that use llog_cat_process with startcat and startidx set (like HSM on master).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 2.12.6 + patches&lt;br/&gt;
Robinhood</environment>
